   </m:math></equation><para id="import-auto-id3256034">The equation “maximum number of electrons that can be in a shell = <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:msup><m:mi>n</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow></m:math>” gives the maximum number in the <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>n</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math> shell to be</para><para id="import-auto-id3246879"><equation id="eip-id3039100"><m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mtext>Maximum number of electrons</m:mtext><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:msup><m:mi>n</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup></m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msup><m:mfenced open="(" close=")"><m:mn>3</m:mn></m:mfenced><m:mrow><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mfenced open="(" close=")"><m:mn>9</m:mn></m:mfenced><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mtext>18.</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math></equation></para><para id="import-auto-id3079798">
      <title>Discussion</title>
    </para>
    <para id="import-auto-id1954742">The total number of electrons in the three possible subshells is thus the same as the formula <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:msup><m:mi>n</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow></m:math>. In standard (spectroscopic) notation, a filled <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>n</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math> shell is denoted as <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:msup><m:mi>s</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:msup><m:mi>p</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mn>6</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:msup><m:mi>d</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mtext>10</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:msup></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math>.  Shells do not fill in a simple manner. Before the <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>n</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math> shell is completely filled, for example, we begin to find electrons in the <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>n</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math> shell.</para></example>

  </section>

