</m:math> shell, what is the spectroscopic notation for this atom?</para></problem></exercise>

    <exercise id="fs-id1412034" type="problems-exercises"><problem id="fs-id1412035">
        <para id="import-auto-id3043928">(a) If one subshell of an atom has 9 electrons in it, what is the minimum value of <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>l</m:mi></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math>?  (b) What is the spectroscopic notation for this atom, if this subshell is part of the <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>n</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math> shell?</para>
